      • deleteFormPattern

        public static void deleteFormPattern(FormPattern formPattern)
        Deletes the given form pattern and commits the change immediately. Should not throw an exception unless there is a low level database error, but if there is such an error the form pattern will not be deleted.
        Parameters:
        formPattern - the form pattern to be deleted

      • getCustomFormInferenceClass

        public static java.lang.String getCustomFormInferenceClass(java.lang.String formPatternCode)
        If the FormPattern denoted by formPatternCode has an entry in the custom_form_inference system table, returns the fully-qualified name of the form inference class from there.
        Parameters:
        formPatternCode - The Code of the FormPattern.
        Returns:
        The fully-qualified class name of the FormPattern's associated custom form inference class, or null if none.

      • findPotentialInferenceForms

        public static java.util.List<FormPattern> findPotentialInferenceForms(PolicyPeriod period,
                                                                      FormInferenceTime[] inferenceTimes)
        Finds all potential form patterns that could apply to the period, given the set of inference times and the job on the period. This just does a very coarse first-level pass, as any date or state-based availability calculations have to be done on a per-slice, per-state, per-pattern basis later on during the creation of the FormData objects.
